</head>
<body>
    <!-- This is a comment: My First Web Page -->
    <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
    <p>This is a simple HTML page to demonstrate basic concepts.</p>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>HTML stands for <strong>HyperText Markup Language</strong> and is used to structure web pages.</p>

    <h2>Text Formatting</h2>
    <p><b>Bold Text</b> and <i>Italic Text</i> are commonly used for emphasis.</p>
    <p><u>Underlined Text</u> and <mark>Highlighted Text</mark> add visual appeal.</p>

    <h2>Quotations</h2>
    <p>Here is a famous quote:</p>
    <blockquote>"The only limit to our realization of tomorrow is our doubts of today." - Franklin D. Roosevelt</blockquote>
    
    <h2>HTML Comments</h2>
    <p>Comments are not visible in the browser but help developers understand the code.</p>
